    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Design decisions and implementation details for F26 Confluence Migration. Covers the 6-step migration pipeline, sliding window chunking, local model recommendations, pause/resume checkpointing, and page hierarchy preservation." .

<urn:reckons:arch/TtlGapDiscovery>
    rdfs:label "Gap: Discovery Without Prior Knowledge" ;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <urn:reckons:arch/TtlVsMarkdownGaps> ;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Markdown: Glob docs/*.md shows all docs. TTL via MCP: must know what to search for. Mitigation: kb_list_entities gives full entity list, kb_stats gives overview, CLAUDE.md lists which graphs exist and their purpose. The hub TTL (starter-guide.ttl) provides a table of contents." ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Concept> .

<urn:reckons:arch/StaticDeployment>
    rdfs:label "Static Deployment" ;
    rdf:type <urn:kbase:type/Concept> ;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "SvelteKit adapter-static produces a pure client-side build. No server-side runtime in production. Deployable to any static host (Netlify, Vercel, GitHub Pages, local file server). Vite dev server provides HMR during development only." ;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broader> <urn:reckons:arch/LocalFirstArch> .

